WEBVTT

00:08.290 --> 00:11.920
[ Cellphone rings ]

00:11.920 --> 00:14.420
Cyrus!
White House Switchboard!

00:14.420 --> 00:16.920
[ Sighs ]
Blue or red?

00:16.920 --> 00:18.540
You gonna get that?

00:18.540 --> 00:20.420
It can wait. In 20 minutes,
I'll be at the White House.

00:20.420 --> 00:21.960
19 if you'll tell me
which tie to wear.

00:21.960 --> 00:24.750
[ Ringing stops ]

00:24.750 --> 00:25.960
What?

00:25.960 --> 00:27.830
[ Laughing ] What?

00:27.830 --> 00:29.380
Do I seem nervous?

00:29.380 --> 00:30.920
You seem...you.
[ Sighs ]

00:30.920 --> 00:33.540
For the first time since
election night, you seem you.

00:33.540 --> 00:34.540
I like it.

00:34.540 --> 00:35.920
[ Sighs deeply ]

00:35.920 --> 00:36.960
Mr. President.

00:38.880 --> 00:39.750
[ Cellphone rings ]

00:39.750 --> 00:40.790
Aah!

00:40.790 --> 00:43.000
Cyrus Beene.

00:43.000 --> 00:44.040
Are your
shades closed?

00:44.040 --> 00:45.750
What? Shades?
I don't have shades.

00:45.750 --> 00:47.790
I have
handmade Venetian blinds.
Whatever.

00:47.790 --> 00:49.120
Close them
and lock your door.

00:49.120 --> 00:50.290
Red --

00:50.290 --> 00:52.000
Shut down your Wi-Fi,
lawyer up, get a handler,

00:52.000 --> 00:53.580
a fixer,
someone to talk for you,

00:53.580 --> 00:56.500
because in 30 seconds,
you no longer talk to anyone.

00:56.500 --> 00:58.170
I voted against it.

00:58.170 --> 00:59.670
[ Chatter,
camera shutters clicking ]

00:59.670 --> 01:01.790
Good morning.

01:01.790 --> 01:03.750
The FBI
is expanding the investigation

01:03.750 --> 01:06.080
into the death
of Governor Francisco Vargas.

01:06.080 --> 01:07.420
Are you saying
that Nelson McClintock

01:07.420 --> 01:09.080
didn't shoot
Frankie Vargas?

01:09.080 --> 01:10.670
Is he --
Not at all.

01:10.670 --> 01:12.000
We're simply opening the scope
of the investigation.

01:12.000 --> 01:14.040
To include who?
Anyone and everyone.

01:14.040 --> 01:15.210
Even Cyrus Beene?

01:15.210 --> 01:16.330
♪♪

01:16.330 --> 01:18.380
Anyone and everyone.

01:18.380 --> 01:20.040
[ Reporters shouting ]
Get Ella.
Take her upstairs.

01:20.040 --> 01:21.790
Woman: So Cyrus Beene
is a suspect in the murder
of his running mate?

01:21.790 --> 01:23.750
Ella, away, now!
Anyone and everyone.

01:23.750 --> 01:25.250
That's all I have to say
at this time,

01:25.250 --> 01:27.750
and now I'd like to introduce
our FBI Director,

01:27.750 --> 01:30.210
Angela Webster, who will be
heading the investigation.

01:30.210 --> 01:32.170
Man: Are you investigating
Cyrus Beene?

01:32.170 --> 01:33.920
Angela: I can't comment on that
at this time.

01:35.210 --> 01:36.290
Mr. Beene!

01:36.290 --> 01:39.500
[ Reporters shouting ]

01:39.500 --> 01:42.710
♪♪

01:52.040 --> 01:54.250
Now we have no VP.
I know the perfect guy.

01:54.250 --> 01:55.670
[ Cheers and applause ]

01:55.670 --> 01:57.830
[ Gunshot ]
Woman: Cyrus Beene!

01:57.830 --> 01:59.830
Man: Fire! Fire!

01:59.830 --> 02:01.120
[ Gunshots ]

02:01.120 --> 02:02.420
My name
is Jennifer Fields.

02:02.420 --> 02:05.210
It was Cyrus Beene.
He killed Frankie Vargas.

02:05.210 --> 02:07.620
The moment I'm elected
President of the United States,

02:07.620 --> 02:09.170
my first
order of business

02:09.170 --> 02:11.540
will be to put you in
the coldest jail cell possible.

02:11.540 --> 02:13.210
300 hours
of Jennifer's footage,

02:13.210 --> 02:15.670
2,200 hours of the security feed
from Vargas headquarters...

02:15.670 --> 02:18.880
And 27 billion Instagram videos
from the campaign.

02:18.880 --> 02:21.380
Now every idiot
with a smartphone
thinks he's Ken Burns.

02:21.380 --> 02:23.750
You know, I've got a little film
project in mind myself.

02:23.750 --> 02:25.880
Yeah?
You, me, Barbados,
and a camcorder.

02:25.880 --> 02:27.170
I was
in Barbados once.

02:27.170 --> 02:28.960
Charlie, we are not
making a sex tape.

02:28.960 --> 02:30.920
We were trying to weaponize
Dengue Fever.

02:30.920 --> 02:32.540
Who said anything
about a sex tape?

02:32.540 --> 02:34.170
This is a romance film,
Robin.

02:34.170 --> 02:36.790
Bubble baths,
walks down on the beach,

02:36.790 --> 02:38.790
firing rounds
at the gun range...

02:38.790 --> 02:40.380
I mean,
if sex comes up...

02:40.380 --> 02:42.250
You're crazy.

02:42.250 --> 02:45.170
Uh, we need to focus!

02:45.170 --> 02:47.000
We still don't know what Cyrus
and Frankie's fight was about.

02:47.000 --> 02:48.120
Right.

02:48.120 --> 02:49.620
So, I started putting together
a timeline.

02:49.620 --> 02:51.620
Jennifer's footage starts
on October 4th.

02:51.620 --> 02:53.920
October 4th?
Wait.

02:53.920 --> 02:57.620
October 4th,
October 4th...

02:57.620 --> 03:00.830
was the day Cyrus won
the vice presidential debates.

03:00.830 --> 03:05.080
♪♪

03:05.080 --> 03:08.120
Admiral Ballard didn't have
a problem with free college

03:08.120 --> 03:09.620
when it was
his college.

03:09.620 --> 03:12.250
He just doesn't want
other Americans

03:12.250 --> 03:15.040
to have the same opportunities
he had.

03:15.040 --> 03:17.170
Admiral Ballard,
given your roots,

03:17.170 --> 03:19.380
I expected a little more
from you.

03:19.380 --> 03:21.330
[ Cheers and applause ]

03:21.330 --> 03:23.620
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

03:23.620 --> 03:25.170
All of you,
celebrate fast.

03:25.170 --> 03:27.000
5:00 a.m.,
on the bus.
[ Woman laughs ]

03:27.000 --> 03:30.750
♪♪

03:42.380 --> 03:44.120
[ Laughing ]

03:44.120 --> 03:45.420
Hey.

03:45.420 --> 03:46.540
My man!

03:46.540 --> 03:48.580
Every network
is calling it for you. TKO.

03:48.580 --> 03:50.210
Brilliant stuff.
Who is this?

03:50.210 --> 03:52.040
You really hammered Ballard
on NAFTA.

03:52.040 --> 03:53.750
Made him sweat like Nixon
in '60.

03:53.750 --> 03:55.330
[ Both laugh ]
Who are you?

03:55.330 --> 03:57.000
Jennifer Fields.

03:57.000 --> 03:58.540
Jenny's the newest member
of our team.

03:58.540 --> 04:00.460
Fresh out of Harvard,
top of her class.

04:00.460 --> 04:02.790
I studied film
and visual studies at Harvard.

04:02.790 --> 04:04.960
Harvard, yes, got it.
She's joining us
on the road.

04:04.960 --> 04:06.330
We have
a videographer now.

04:06.330 --> 04:08.620
Jennifer: Someone has to
document this historic run.

04:08.620 --> 04:10.460
We're electing
the first Latino President

04:10.460 --> 04:11.580
in our nation's history.

04:11.580 --> 04:13.380
I'm gonna get Jenny --
uh, Jennifer --

04:13.380 --> 04:14.620
set up
with our media folks.

04:14.620 --> 04:15.750
Come on.
Wonderful meeting you.

04:15.750 --> 04:19.290
♪♪

04:19.290 --> 04:22.170
David Rosen!

04:22.170 --> 04:25.710
The Attorney General
of the United States.

04:25.710 --> 04:27.290
No!
I will not --

04:27.290 --> 04:30.080
[ Groans ]

04:30.080 --> 04:31.540
Okay.

04:32.960 --> 04:35.380
I am being set up
by Olivia Pope.

04:35.380 --> 04:38.880
She is trying to frame me
for murdering Frankie.

04:38.880 --> 04:42.290
She is trying
to steal the presidency.

04:42.290 --> 04:43.920
That is
what is going on here,

04:43.920 --> 04:46.500
and I am not going to
let it happen, okay?

04:46.500 --> 04:48.960
Now, I just need to take
a minute and make some calls.

04:48.960 --> 04:50.620
I will get this
figured out.

04:50.620 --> 04:53.120
And to answer
your question --

04:53.120 --> 04:56.580
no,
I didn't do it.

04:56.580 --> 04:58.540
I didn't
ask you that.

04:58.540 --> 05:00.290
Yes.

05:00.290 --> 05:02.920
You did.

05:02.920 --> 05:05.670
♪♪

05:08.250 --> 05:09.380
[ Crashing ]

05:09.380 --> 05:11.540
Man: What are you doing
back here, ma'am?

05:11.540 --> 05:12.830
Woman:
Let go of me!

05:12.830 --> 05:14.540
I know him!
I know him!

05:14.540 --> 05:15.920
Oh, thank God.

05:15.920 --> 05:17.790
Tell them --
we're friends.

05:17.790 --> 05:19.460
♪♪

05:19.460 --> 05:20.710
Cyrus!

05:20.710 --> 05:22.460
I crawled across the lawn
to get here.

05:22.460 --> 05:24.830
My hands
touched the ground.

05:24.830 --> 05:26.330
Let me in.

05:26.330 --> 05:28.040
♪♪

05:28.040 --> 05:29.250
What do you want,
Liz?

05:29.250 --> 05:31.420
What do I want?
[ Sighs ]

05:31.420 --> 05:32.710
I want to help.

05:32.710 --> 05:34.330
No. No, you don't.
I know you.

05:34.330 --> 05:35.830
You're not
the helping kind.

05:35.830 --> 05:37.040
You're a snake.

05:37.040 --> 05:39.290
You are literally...

05:39.290 --> 05:40.290
a snake
in the grass.

05:40.290 --> 05:42.620
Whatever it is
that you want, no!

05:42.620 --> 05:46.040
How many times have you called
David Rosen this morning?

05:46.040 --> 05:48.460
Uh, let me guess -- 2, 3, 6?
Did he take your call?

05:48.460 --> 05:51.170
Has anyone
taken your call?

05:51.170 --> 05:53.250
Here's what I know.

05:53.250 --> 05:55.830
I know that you are
absolutely screwed right now.

05:55.830 --> 05:57.580
I know the press
is ready to hang you,

05:57.580 --> 05:59.210
and without someone
in your corner,

05:59.210 --> 06:01.380
you will never
be President.

06:01.380 --> 06:03.540
So what do I want?

06:03.540 --> 06:06.250
I want
to help you.

06:06.250 --> 06:08.250
[ Sighs ] And?

06:08.250 --> 06:09.830
And what?

06:09.830 --> 06:11.040
And how
do you want to help you?

06:11.040 --> 06:12.920
Chief of Staff.

06:15.580 --> 06:17.920
Fine.
Good.

06:17.920 --> 06:19.790
Let's get you a meeting
with the president.

06:19.790 --> 06:23.080
Now, how did this happen
and why?

06:23.080 --> 06:25.420
Liv!

06:25.420 --> 06:27.540
Cyrus.
[ Sighs ]

06:27.540 --> 06:29.250
Nice work tonight.

06:29.250 --> 06:31.040
[ Chuckles ]

06:31.040 --> 06:33.250
Well, your guy
didn't make it easy for me,

06:33.250 --> 06:34.830
that's for sure.
Yeah, he did.
[ Chuckles ]

06:34.830 --> 06:35.830
We have
some work to do,

06:35.830 --> 06:38.250
but still,
that was impressive.

06:38.250 --> 06:39.710
You were impressive.

06:39.710 --> 06:41.710
Thank you.

06:41.710 --> 06:43.620
I miss you.

06:45.500 --> 06:46.790
[ Inhales sharply ]

06:46.790 --> 06:48.460
When all of this
is over,

06:48.460 --> 06:50.580
let's get
a bottle of du Bellay,

06:50.580 --> 06:51.880
meet at
the Lincoln Memorial,

06:51.880 --> 06:53.580
and drink about this,
because...

06:53.580 --> 06:54.580
[ Both laugh ]
I know.

06:56.250 --> 06:58.620
You're surprised?

06:58.620 --> 06:59.880
What?

06:59.880 --> 07:02.540
You're surprised
that I'm impressive.

07:02.540 --> 07:05.120
"You were impressive" --
you were surprised.

07:05.120 --> 07:07.330
It was a compliment,
Cy.

07:07.330 --> 07:08.540
Was it?
Yes.

07:08.540 --> 07:09.710
How?

07:09.710 --> 07:10.960
What?

07:10.960 --> 07:13.170
How was it
a compliment?

07:15.830 --> 07:19.790
I'm saying
you've changed,

07:19.790 --> 07:21.790
you've evolved,
you've grown.

07:21.790 --> 07:23.880
You've gotten good
at this.

07:23.880 --> 07:25.170
So I'm no longer

07:25.170 --> 07:28.540
the troll under the bridge
who grunts and snorts,

07:28.540 --> 07:30.120
there's lipstick
on this pig now,

07:30.120 --> 07:31.750
and look at
the monkey dance?

07:31.750 --> 07:33.210
That doesn't even
make sense.

07:33.210 --> 07:34.420
Yes, it does.

07:34.420 --> 07:36.120
It does.

07:38.500 --> 07:41.250
Okay.
I'm surprised.

07:42.920 --> 07:44.830
I didn't think
it would work.

07:44.830 --> 07:46.460
I was wrong.

07:46.460 --> 07:49.040
I'm saying
I was wrong.

07:49.040 --> 07:50.250
Look at you.

07:50.250 --> 07:51.960
You've bloomed.

07:51.960 --> 07:54.120
So maybe putting yourself
on Frankie's ticket

07:54.120 --> 07:55.290
wasn't the worst --

07:55.290 --> 07:56.830
Putting myself
on the ticket?

07:58.500 --> 08:00.290
I put myself
on the ticket?

08:00.290 --> 08:01.380
That's what you think?

08:01.380 --> 08:04.120
Well...

08:04.120 --> 08:06.330
[ Laughs ]
Come on, Cyrus.

08:06.330 --> 08:08.170
I put myself
on the ticket?

08:09.830 --> 08:13.290
Are we going to pretend
that...?

08:13.290 --> 08:14.460
It's me.

08:14.460 --> 08:16.290
I know you.
We both know.

08:16.290 --> 08:17.880
I made his policies,

08:17.880 --> 08:21.080
I hid his secrets,
I ran his country.

08:21.080 --> 08:23.080
Watched the two of you
grope each other

08:23.080 --> 08:24.080
like a cheap porno.

08:24.080 --> 08:26.960
And none of you
ever saw me.

08:26.960 --> 08:28.120
And that's fine.

08:28.120 --> 08:30.580
You think
what you want to think of me.

08:30.580 --> 08:33.170
I certainly have all kinds
of opinions about Olivia Pope.

08:33.170 --> 08:35.830
So you believe
whatever you want.

08:35.830 --> 08:36.960
But this?

08:36.960 --> 08:38.960
Me putting myself
on the Democratic ticket

08:38.960 --> 08:41.080
for Vice President
of these United States --

08:41.080 --> 08:44.250
don't you ever say that
out loud...

08:44.250 --> 08:46.380
ever...

08:46.380 --> 08:48.460
again.

08:48.460 --> 08:51.830
I don't know what you did
to manipulate Frankie,

08:51.830 --> 08:53.290
what angle you used,

08:53.290 --> 08:57.040
what you blackmailed him with
to put yourself on that ticket

08:57.040 --> 09:00.790
and I don't care,
but America will care.

09:00.790 --> 09:04.170
So I'm gonna dig
until I find something.

09:04.170 --> 09:06.620
♪♪

09:06.620 --> 09:08.540
You better
watch yourself.

09:10.210 --> 09:12.790
Goodbye, Olivia.

09:12.790 --> 09:17.580
♪♪

09:42.000 --> 09:43.420
Abby.

09:49.080 --> 09:50.830
Fine.
You're wrong.

09:50.830 --> 09:52.790
I'm not wrong.
You're wrong!

09:52.790 --> 09:56.250
Sir, opening up this
investigation into Cyrus Beene

09:56.250 --> 09:58.620
based on
some random voicemail

09:58.620 --> 09:59.830
and 20 seconds
of video footage

09:59.830 --> 10:01.710
that's clearly
been taken out of context --

10:01.710 --> 10:02.830
I made
a decision.

10:02.830 --> 10:04.620
This news
is less than a day old,

10:04.620 --> 10:06.670
and already the Dow
has dropped 400 points.

10:06.670 --> 10:08.420
Our global markets
are in a freefall.

10:08.420 --> 10:10.880
The world is clamoring to know
what the hell is going on,

10:10.880 --> 10:12.250
and we can't tell them.

10:12.250 --> 10:14.620
We can't tell them that the
President of the United States

10:14.620 --> 10:17.040
has allowed his ex-mistress
to brainwash him into thinking

10:17.040 --> 10:18.960
his former Chief of Staff
is a murderer --

10:18.960 --> 10:22.330
Watch yourself.
You are being played.

10:23.380 --> 10:26.170
[ Door opens, closes ]

10:27.880 --> 10:29.380
This election
is all about you.

10:29.380 --> 10:31.380
It's all about what
your future's gonna look like.

10:31.380 --> 10:34.460
So this November, stay woke.
Vote.

10:34.460 --> 10:36.580
How was that, Jenny?

10:36.580 --> 10:38.040
Jennifer:
[ Laughing ] "Woke"?

10:38.040 --> 10:39.420
Pretty good, huh?
My daughter taught it to me.

10:39.420 --> 10:41.210
Please don't.
For her sake.
No?

10:41.210 --> 10:43.460
All right, how about...

10:43.460 --> 10:46.540
My free-college program
is on fleek.

10:46.540 --> 10:47.710
No.

10:47.710 --> 10:50.290
[ Scoffs ] Okay, okay.

10:50.290 --> 10:52.170
How about, "Greetings, youths,

10:52.170 --> 10:55.040
this is prehistoric talking
fossil Frankie Vargas..."

10:55.040 --> 10:56.500
They were
sleeping together.

10:56.500 --> 10:58.920
Totally. Only explanation.
Because that wasn't funny.

10:58.920 --> 11:01.120
Man, must've been real annoying
for their co-workers.

11:01.120 --> 11:02.620
Talk to her friends.
I want to know if and when

11:02.620 --> 11:04.750
Cyrus found out
about Frankie and Jennifer

11:04.750 --> 11:06.750
and what he did
about it.

11:16.170 --> 11:17.920
Thank you for coming.

11:21.540 --> 11:24.460
This can now go
either one of two ways.

11:24.460 --> 11:27.000
We can finish
the investigation

11:27.000 --> 11:30.710
and you will be arrested,
tried, convicted, and executed

11:30.710 --> 11:32.420
for the assassination
of Frankie Vargas.

11:34.290 --> 11:37.380
Or you can step down.

11:37.380 --> 11:38.880
Withdraw.

11:38.880 --> 11:40.330
Health, grief, whatever --
it doesn't matter.

11:40.330 --> 11:43.920
In exchange for which --
for the good of the country --

11:43.920 --> 11:48.580
I'll make the investigation
go away and you'll be cleared,

11:48.580 --> 11:50.670
and you can live out
the rest of your days

11:50.670 --> 11:52.460
in whatever peace
you can find.

11:54.460 --> 11:56.500
Those are the options.

12:00.040 --> 12:02.290
[ Laughing ]

12:02.290 --> 12:03.460
Oh...

12:07.120 --> 12:09.080
You...

12:09.080 --> 12:11.500
really think
I killed Frankie?

12:11.500 --> 12:12.960
It doesn't matter
what I think.

12:12.960 --> 12:13.960
It matters to me.

12:13.960 --> 12:15.380
It's time
to make a deal, Cyrus.

12:15.380 --> 12:17.250
It's a simple
yes or no question.

12:17.250 --> 12:19.330
You are not in a position
to be asking me questions.

12:19.330 --> 12:21.830
You want
to make a deal?

12:21.830 --> 12:23.210
Okay.

12:23.210 --> 12:25.460
How about this?

12:25.460 --> 12:30.040
I'll withdraw right now
if Mellie does.

12:31.460 --> 12:33.540
We'll put this
all behind us,

12:33.540 --> 12:35.670
let the country
pick a new president.

12:37.330 --> 12:39.040
Call Liv.

12:39.040 --> 12:41.540
See what she says.

12:41.540 --> 12:42.620
I don't need
to call Liv.

12:44.290 --> 12:45.830
No, you don't.

12:45.830 --> 12:49.620
Be-- Because you -- you know
what she's going to say.

12:49.620 --> 12:53.120
She'd never give up her chance
at the Oval.

12:53.120 --> 12:56.210
She's not interested
in justice or truth.

12:56.210 --> 12:58.580
She's not interested

12:58.580 --> 13:01.290
in doing what's best
for the country.

13:01.290 --> 13:02.880
She just wants
to win.

13:02.880 --> 13:04.880
This isn't about Liv.

13:04.880 --> 13:06.380
[ Laughs ]

13:09.210 --> 13:11.210
Of every offensive thing
you've ever said to me,

13:11.210 --> 13:14.170
that might be the worst because
that insults my intelligence.

13:14.170 --> 13:15.830
I'm not withdrawing.

13:15.830 --> 13:18.210
For the good
of the country.

13:18.210 --> 13:23.420
Remember what you
so generously handed me

13:23.420 --> 13:24.790
the night
that Frankie was shot,

13:24.790 --> 13:28.790
what you called the most
beautiful thing in the world?

13:28.790 --> 13:29.920
America?

13:29.920 --> 13:31.580
I'm keeping it.

13:31.580 --> 13:34.290
It's not safe
with you.

13:34.290 --> 13:37.250
♪♪

13:38.880 --> 13:41.880
[ Sighs ]

13:41.880 --> 13:45.960
"For the good
of the country."

13:45.960 --> 13:48.330
I'll tell you what's good
for the country, Fitz --

13:48.330 --> 13:49.920
you resigning
from office.

13:49.920 --> 13:51.210
My guess?

13:51.210 --> 13:53.920
We're out of the woods
by the end of the week.

13:53.920 --> 13:56.960
No way he can keep
this investigation going

13:56.960 --> 13:58.210
with that kind of press
out there.

13:59.830 --> 14:01.540
Michael: Wha--

14:01.540 --> 14:03.580
You don't think I forgot.
It's book time!

14:03.580 --> 14:05.540
See? I told you
everything will work out...

14:05.540 --> 14:07.040
Mr. President.

14:07.040 --> 14:08.540
[ Chuckles ]

14:08.540 --> 14:09.750
[ Sighs ]

14:14.750 --> 14:15.790
[ Cellphone rings ]

14:16.830 --> 14:18.460
[ Sighs ]

14:18.460 --> 14:20.880
[ Cellphone beeps ]

14:20.880 --> 14:22.580
Y'ello.

14:22.580 --> 14:25.460
Tom:
Hey, Cy.

14:25.460 --> 14:26.710
Tom?

14:26.710 --> 14:29.500
You do
remember my name.

14:29.500 --> 14:31.170
I thought since
maybe I hadn't heard from you,

14:31.170 --> 14:32.250
you might have forgotten.

14:36.290 --> 14:38.330
You shouldn't
be calling me.

14:38.330 --> 14:41.040
You didn't think I'd just
stay in my hole, did you?

14:41.040 --> 14:42.920
Maybe you did.

14:42.920 --> 14:46.080
Maybe you think so little of me
that it never occurred to you

14:46.080 --> 14:49.170
that I might have my own stakes
in all of this.

14:49.170 --> 14:51.540
Listen to me,
Tom --

14:51.540 --> 14:52.880
You used me,
Cy.

14:52.880 --> 14:54.500
I didn't use you.

14:54.500 --> 14:57.460
You used me,
and you hurt me.

14:57.460 --> 14:58.580
Again.

14:58.580 --> 15:02.540
And now I have this tightness
in my chest,

15:02.540 --> 15:04.290
and the only thing
that makes me feel any better,

15:04.290 --> 15:07.500
the only thought that
gives me a shred of comfort,

15:07.500 --> 15:09.250
is the knowledge
that at any moment,

15:09.250 --> 15:11.880
I can take everything
away from you

15:11.880 --> 15:14.380
simply by opening
my mouth.

15:14.380 --> 15:16.830
I'm gonna
make this right, Tom.

15:16.830 --> 15:19.330
I promise.

15:19.330 --> 15:21.710
Tom?

15:21.710 --> 15:25.710
♪♪

15:28.790 --> 15:31.580
[ Cellphone slams ]

15:48.120 --> 15:49.460
Stop!

15:49.460 --> 15:51.210
Back off!

15:51.210 --> 15:53.080
911!
I just want
to talk.

15:53.080 --> 15:54.500
Oh. [ Chuckles ]

15:54.500 --> 15:56.460
Why didn't you
say so?

15:56.460 --> 15:59.040
In that case --
Eyes! Elbow!

15:59.040 --> 16:00.210
Hey, hey!

16:00.210 --> 16:01.920
I'm not here
to hurt you.

16:01.920 --> 16:03.040
Okay?

16:03.040 --> 16:04.540
Groin!!

16:04.540 --> 16:05.750
Hey, hey, hey!

16:07.000 --> 16:08.960
I'm here
to help you.

16:08.960 --> 16:12.080
You were friends
with Jennifer Fields.

16:12.080 --> 16:14.960
I told Jenny you never, ever
get involved with your boss,

16:14.960 --> 16:17.540
especially when your boss
is running for President.

16:17.540 --> 16:19.380
But she really
liked him.

16:19.380 --> 16:22.460
She used to tell me how much
she enjoyed being around him,

16:22.460 --> 16:24.580
how much he used to
make her laugh.

16:24.580 --> 16:25.750
And, then...

16:25.750 --> 16:26.750
Then she got fired.

16:26.750 --> 16:28.580
Fired?

16:28.580 --> 16:30.330
♪♪

16:30.330 --> 16:33.000
Does this
look like fired to you?

16:33.000 --> 16:34.420
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

16:34.420 --> 16:36.830
So, the man
who beat up Jennifer --

16:36.830 --> 16:38.290
was it Cyrus Beene?

16:40.210 --> 16:43.620
This guy
was much more terrifying.

16:43.620 --> 16:46.250
♪♪

16:55.790 --> 16:57.170
[ Inhales sharply ]

16:57.170 --> 17:00.460
I'm only in D.C.
for 36 hours and...

17:00.460 --> 17:02.460
I missed you,
Tom.

17:02.460 --> 17:03.790
You abandoned me.

17:05.540 --> 17:07.120
As soon
as they put you on the ticket.

17:21.580 --> 17:23.880
I watched your debate.

17:23.880 --> 17:26.460
You were brilliant.

17:26.460 --> 17:28.500
Presidential.

17:28.500 --> 17:31.380
You guys are winning?

17:31.380 --> 17:32.880
Yes.
That's good.

17:32.880 --> 17:34.330
Maybe.
Maybe?

17:34.330 --> 17:36.170
I've been here before.

17:36.170 --> 17:38.750
[ Laughing ]
These people...

17:38.750 --> 17:40.620
the candidates...

17:40.620 --> 17:42.250
Frankie seems different.

17:42.250 --> 17:43.580
Ha.

17:43.580 --> 17:46.330
He's more like Fitz
than I ever could have imagined.

17:46.330 --> 17:47.380
One adoring glance

17:47.380 --> 17:49.620
from some Harvard twit
with a camera...

17:49.620 --> 17:52.460
and he's under
a spell.

17:52.460 --> 17:57.920
I've tried to separate him
from this woman, but...no.

17:59.290 --> 18:01.540
We're this...

18:01.540 --> 18:04.080
We're this close.

18:04.080 --> 18:06.330
You hear me?
Do you realize?

18:06.330 --> 18:10.540
I am this close
to the Vice Presidency,

18:10.540 --> 18:13.710
and this girl is going to
cost me what I have earned,

18:13.710 --> 18:16.500
what I have...
bled out for,

18:16.500 --> 18:19.170
what I have literally
killed for.

18:21.250 --> 18:22.580
I could.

18:25.620 --> 18:28.080
You could what?

18:28.080 --> 18:29.420
Take care of the girl.

18:29.420 --> 18:31.420
Make her back away
from the campaign.

18:31.420 --> 18:33.710
That's not...

18:33.710 --> 18:36.540
why I called you here.

18:36.540 --> 18:38.250
[ Sighs ]

18:38.250 --> 18:39.620
What's her name?

18:39.620 --> 18:40.830
[ Sighs ]

18:40.830 --> 18:42.120
Maybe...

18:42.120 --> 18:45.080
there's something
I'm not seeing.

18:45.080 --> 18:46.920
Another angle?
What's her name?

18:46.920 --> 18:48.500
Maybe...

18:48.500 --> 18:50.920
there's nothing going on,
and I'm just being paranoid --

18:50.920 --> 18:52.250
Shh!

18:52.250 --> 18:55.120
Just give me
her name.

18:59.420 --> 19:00.880
Jennifer Fields.

19:02.540 --> 19:05.620
Can we
get out of here now?

19:07.080 --> 19:09.500
Because I'm pretty sure
this place is not serving

19:09.500 --> 19:14.420
what I've been craving
for a long, long time, Cyrus.

19:18.040 --> 19:20.710
[ Laughs ]

19:20.710 --> 19:23.250
We're lucky she didn't
understand what it meant!

19:23.250 --> 19:25.250
I mean,
who tells a 6-year-old

19:25.250 --> 19:26.790
that she doesn't have
what it takes to be a scientist?

19:26.790 --> 19:27.920
I'm in trouble.

19:27.920 --> 19:29.710
A racist,
that's who.

19:29.710 --> 19:30.830
Ella's smart --

19:30.830 --> 19:32.420
smarter than most of the kids
in her class.

19:32.420 --> 19:33.580
[ Breathing heavily ]

19:33.580 --> 19:35.040
And that teacher of hers,
I let her have it.

19:35.040 --> 19:36.710
I'm...
When you
are president...

19:36.710 --> 19:38.040
I'm in trouble,
Michael.

19:38.040 --> 19:41.250
...you're gonna do something
about the pervasive bias

19:41.250 --> 19:42.960
towards children of color
in the educational system.

19:42.960 --> 19:44.250
Michael,
I'm in trouble.

19:44.250 --> 19:46.250
I mean, what if -- what if Ella
was at public school?

19:46.250 --> 19:48.580
That -- That teacher
would've gotten away with j--

19:48.580 --> 19:50.000
Michael.

19:50.000 --> 19:51.210
What is it?
Help.

19:51.210 --> 19:52.420
Honey,
what's wrong?

19:54.540 --> 19:56.540
Tom.

19:56.540 --> 20:00.580
♪♪

20:03.120 --> 20:04.880
Please,
would you just -- just --

20:04.880 --> 20:06.960
No, no, no. When you --
When you begged me --

20:06.960 --> 20:11.500
begged me -- to come back,
you -- you said no more Tom.

20:11.500 --> 20:12.540
No more Tom!

20:12.540 --> 20:14.330
You're disgusting.

20:14.330 --> 20:16.790
I screwed up.
I didn't mean to.
Liar.

20:16.790 --> 20:19.540
I believed you.

20:19.540 --> 20:20.920
I love you.

20:20.920 --> 20:23.040
You are mad
and you have every right,

20:23.040 --> 20:24.380
but you can't be mad --
not right now.

20:24.380 --> 20:27.170
Not now.
Tom is back.

20:27.170 --> 20:31.170
And Tom is not
a regular person, Michael.

20:31.170 --> 20:35.620
He's back,
and he's not going to go away.

20:35.620 --> 20:37.710
No,
I -- I-I can't do this.
Mi-Michael,
wait, please!

20:37.710 --> 20:38.920
Please!

20:38.920 --> 20:39.920
I know...

20:39.920 --> 20:43.170
I've hurt you
in unimaginable ways.

20:43.170 --> 20:44.790
I am sorry.

20:44.790 --> 20:47.290
I am so, so sorry.

20:47.290 --> 20:52.500
I don't want --
want to be a bad person.

20:52.500 --> 20:56.920
I -- I am not --
not a bad person.

20:56.920 --> 20:59.540
I've just made mistakes.

20:59.540 --> 21:02.580
This --
This whole thing,

21:02.580 --> 21:04.920
it's all because
I made a mistake.

21:06.920 --> 21:09.500
I made
a horrible mistake.

21:11.170 --> 21:13.380
Cyrus,
what did you do?

21:13.380 --> 21:16.380
♪♪

21:17.620 --> 21:19.500
Did you kill
Frankie Vargas?

21:24.540 --> 21:25.830
No.

21:25.830 --> 21:27.500
Don't tell me.

21:27.500 --> 21:29.750
I don't want
to know.

21:29.750 --> 21:32.500
I don't ever want
to know.

21:32.500 --> 21:35.000
♪♪

21:40.790 --> 21:41.960
[ Knock on door ]
Is it done?

21:44.880 --> 21:48.120
Jennifer Fields will no longer
be a problem.

21:48.120 --> 21:49.880
[ Door closes ]

21:51.170 --> 21:52.960
Tom,
she's a civilian.

21:52.960 --> 21:55.250
I wanted her gone,
but not --

21:55.250 --> 21:56.290
Barely had to
raise my voice.

21:56.290 --> 21:57.960
[ Sighs ]

21:57.960 --> 22:00.170
[ Laughs ]

22:00.170 --> 22:01.330
[ Sighs ]

22:01.330 --> 22:02.670
Aah-aah!

22:02.670 --> 22:05.880
We --
Get that coat off.

22:05.880 --> 22:08.710
We're celebrating.

22:10.040 --> 22:12.210
We really do make
an amazing team...

22:13.500 --> 22:15.040
...don't we, Tommy?

22:15.040 --> 22:16.620
Yeah.

22:16.620 --> 22:19.420
[ Chuckles ]

22:19.420 --> 22:21.080
Mm.

22:22.750 --> 22:24.120
[ Laughs ]

22:24.120 --> 22:26.000
Frankie Vargas...

22:26.000 --> 22:27.040
Mm-hmm.

22:27.040 --> 22:28.420
...is weak.

22:28.420 --> 22:30.420
He's a normal.

22:30.420 --> 22:33.880
You are
an exceptional man.

22:33.880 --> 22:38.290
[ Chuckles ]
You belong
at the top of the ticket.

22:38.290 --> 22:41.580
Frankie will make
a great president --

22:41.580 --> 22:44.500
Only because
he has you.

22:44.500 --> 22:47.250
You belong
on the throne.

22:47.250 --> 22:49.830
You're a king,
Cyrus.

22:49.830 --> 22:51.580
I can help you
take what's yours.

22:51.580 --> 22:55.170
[ Laughing ]

22:55.170 --> 23:00.420
[ Breathing heavily ]

23:02.580 --> 23:05.330
Do you want it?

23:05.330 --> 23:06.790
What...

23:06.790 --> 23:10.210
W-What are you saying?

23:11.790 --> 23:13.790
You know
what I'm saying.

23:24.380 --> 23:27.120
Frankie's been good
to me.

23:27.120 --> 23:29.960
Then he has done
his service.

23:34.960 --> 23:39.080
♪♪

23:39.080 --> 23:44.750
Do you want to be
President of the United States?

23:46.620 --> 23:51.170
♪♪

24:00.040 --> 24:02.880
I want to be the President
of the United States.

24:08.120 --> 24:11.080
[ Chuckles ]

24:11.080 --> 24:13.380
♪♪

24:13.380 --> 24:15.120
[ Camera shutter clicking ]
Olivia:
Tom Larsen?

24:15.120 --> 24:17.620
QR-24 facial recognition
picked him up on a street cam

24:17.620 --> 24:19.880
in Jennifer's neighborhood
the night she was beaten up.

24:19.880 --> 24:21.710
And he matches
the friend's description.

24:21.710 --> 24:23.290
Okay,
so he's Cyrus' thug.

24:23.290 --> 24:25.750
It doesn't prove Cyrus used him
to kill Frankie that night.

24:25.750 --> 24:27.330
It does if we're able
to put Tom in Philadelphia

24:27.330 --> 24:28.750
the night
of Frankie's shooting.

24:28.750 --> 24:30.210
Start tracking
Tom's movements.

24:30.210 --> 24:32.120
Find out where he was that night
and find out fast, people.

24:32.120 --> 24:33.170
Let's go!

24:34.460 --> 24:36.750
Hey, you wanted
to see me, sir.

24:37.880 --> 24:40.500
I...

24:40.500 --> 24:43.420
I just came
for my camera.

24:43.420 --> 24:44.830
That's it.

24:44.830 --> 24:46.750
Frankie:
Jennifer...

24:46.750 --> 24:50.580
would you excuse us
for a second?

25:00.710 --> 25:03.500
[ Door opens, closes ]

25:10.710 --> 25:13.620
She was a threat
to you, sir.

25:13.620 --> 25:16.500
To --
To your candidacy,

25:16.500 --> 25:18.620
to everything
that we've worked for.
A threat?

25:20.460 --> 25:21.790
Are you serious
right now?

25:21.790 --> 25:24.080
I sa-saw
the two of you, Frankie.

25:24.080 --> 25:26.880
I knew how that story
was gonna end.

25:26.880 --> 25:28.580
Look, what the hell
are you talking about?!

25:29.620 --> 25:32.830
I am
a happily married man, Cyrus!

25:32.830 --> 25:35.080
I love my wife!

25:35.080 --> 25:38.460
Nothing happened
between me and this girl!

25:38.460 --> 25:40.040
Nothing was ever
going to happen!

25:42.250 --> 25:45.120
You disgust me.

25:45.120 --> 25:46.830
The two of us
are done.

25:46.830 --> 25:49.420
Frankie,
don't be ridiculous!

25:49.420 --> 25:51.540
You know that I...

25:51.540 --> 25:55.210
would never do anything
to hurt you.

25:55.210 --> 25:58.540
Everything I do
is to help you --

25:58.540 --> 25:59.750
help us,
help the country.

25:59.750 --> 26:01.960
What you did
is vile!

26:01.960 --> 26:04.460
Inexcusable!

26:04.460 --> 26:06.670
Frankie, please,
you don't understand --

26:06.670 --> 26:08.830
No! What you don't understand
is that the moment

26:08.830 --> 26:11.000
I'm elected
President of the United States,

26:11.000 --> 26:12.830
my first
order of business

26:12.830 --> 26:16.210
will be to throw you in
the coldest jail cell possible!

26:16.210 --> 26:19.500
Over my dead body will you
get away with what you did.

26:19.500 --> 26:21.080
Frankie...

26:21.080 --> 26:22.120
Fr--

26:22.120 --> 26:23.790
[ Sighs ]

26:23.790 --> 26:25.040
Come on.
Come on!

26:25.040 --> 26:26.420
Frank-- Frankie!
[ Door closes ]

26:26.420 --> 26:30.960
♪♪

26:30.960 --> 26:33.120
You almost
killed that girl.

26:33.120 --> 26:35.210
Jenny was a threat
to your presidency.

26:35.210 --> 26:36.620
My...what?

26:36.620 --> 26:38.420
No, she was a threat
to Frankie.

26:38.420 --> 26:40.420
You were supposed to
scare her off.

26:40.420 --> 26:41.750
She was a threat
to you.

26:41.750 --> 26:44.710
Frankie doesn't matter.
He's the vehicle.

26:44.710 --> 26:47.420
We just need to get him
to election night,

26:47.420 --> 26:50.580
and then we are onto
the final piece of the puzzle.

26:50.580 --> 26:52.170
President Beene --

26:52.170 --> 26:53.620
No!
Look at me.

26:53.620 --> 26:55.170
Will you look at me?

26:57.000 --> 27:01.790
You are not to touch a hair
on Frankie Vargas' head.

27:01.790 --> 27:03.250
Is that clear?

27:04.290 --> 27:05.330
Yes, sir!

27:05.330 --> 27:07.250
♪♪

27:07.250 --> 27:09.040
[ Chuckles ]

27:09.040 --> 27:10.710
I get it.

27:10.710 --> 27:12.420
I know
what the plan is.

27:12.420 --> 27:13.960
The scorpion
and the frog.

27:13.960 --> 27:15.580
This all began in Harrisburg,
and it will end in that --

27:15.580 --> 27:16.750
Tom!

27:16.750 --> 27:18.960
No one --
No one is listening!

27:18.960 --> 27:20.330
♪♪

27:20.330 --> 27:21.830
Geez.

27:21.830 --> 27:24.380
You're the one who needs
to start listening.

27:24.380 --> 27:30.250
I am not kidding or pretending
or conspiring here.

27:30.250 --> 27:32.330
I am telling you.

27:35.120 --> 27:37.000
Do not touch him.

27:37.000 --> 27:38.460
You got that?

27:39.710 --> 27:41.710
I need you
to understand!

27:44.920 --> 27:47.420
You don't -- You --
You don't want my help.

27:47.420 --> 27:48.710
I do not want
your help!

27:48.710 --> 27:52.830
I do not want you!
You are dead to me!

27:52.830 --> 27:55.460
You're dead
to yourself!

27:56.750 --> 27:58.460
You're ending this?

27:58.460 --> 28:00.460
It's over,
Tom!

28:00.460 --> 28:01.750
Finished!!

28:01.750 --> 28:03.750
I'm done.

28:03.750 --> 28:09.920
This...is done!

28:11.460 --> 28:14.210
♪♪

28:18.540 --> 28:21.460
[ Reporters shouting ]

28:23.040 --> 28:25.000
[ Lock clicks ]

28:25.000 --> 28:26.460
[ Sighs ]

28:26.460 --> 28:29.880
♪♪

28:56.330 --> 29:00.580
I'll be careful,
okay?

29:00.580 --> 29:04.620
♪♪

29:12.120 --> 29:18.460
[ Crickets chirping ]

29:33.380 --> 29:35.540
President Beene.

29:35.540 --> 29:38.120
Tom? [ Chuckles ]

29:38.120 --> 29:41.580
Thank you f-for coming.

29:41.580 --> 29:42.790
I --

29:42.790 --> 29:45.250
Why -- Why don't you
s-sit down?

29:48.290 --> 29:50.080
I know that I...

29:50.080 --> 29:52.330
treated you badly.

29:52.330 --> 29:55.960
This is about
making up for that.

29:55.960 --> 30:00.920
This is about making sure
we both have a future.

30:00.920 --> 30:03.250
P-Please...
sit down.

30:16.790 --> 30:19.120
[ Sighs ]

30:19.120 --> 30:23.420
[ Breathing heavily ]

30:23.420 --> 30:24.920
We've been through
a lot together,

30:24.920 --> 30:26.330
you and me.

30:26.330 --> 30:29.330
And I know
that we left things badly,

30:29.330 --> 30:30.540
but we've had
a lot of good --

30:30.540 --> 30:32.380
What do you want,
Cyrus?

30:33.790 --> 30:35.290
Going forward,

30:35.290 --> 30:38.380
I need you to stay quiet
about me -- about us.

30:40.580 --> 30:43.170
The way I see it,
we had a...misunderstanding

30:43.170 --> 30:44.500
about the plan,

30:44.500 --> 30:46.420
and I don't blame you
for that.

30:46.420 --> 30:47.500
I don't.

30:47.500 --> 30:49.880
There was a lot going on
with the campaign...

30:49.880 --> 30:51.380
[ Sighs ]

30:51.380 --> 30:52.920
...with us.

30:52.920 --> 30:55.040
We were in love.

30:55.040 --> 30:56.380
[ Chuckles ]

30:59.330 --> 31:02.710
I loved you,
at least.

31:04.380 --> 31:07.330
I was in love...
with you.

31:07.330 --> 31:11.710
That's the one thing
that I'm sure of.

31:11.710 --> 31:13.790
And...

31:13.790 --> 31:17.920
I love you still.

31:17.920 --> 31:20.330
And despite your anger --
rightful anger --

31:20.330 --> 31:23.830
about what happened
between us,

31:23.830 --> 31:27.170
I hope
you can recognize that.

31:27.170 --> 31:28.290
[ Sighs ]

31:29.670 --> 31:31.620
Do you, Tom?

31:31.620 --> 31:36.080
Know -- Know that
throughout everything,

31:36.080 --> 31:37.040
I always loved you?

31:37.040 --> 31:39.620
Ruff ruff!

31:39.620 --> 31:42.080
Ruff ruff!

31:43.120 --> 31:44.580
[ Chuckles ]

31:44.580 --> 31:46.620
You think I'm a dog.

31:46.620 --> 31:48.290
What? No --

31:48.290 --> 31:50.120
Who comes
when he's called.

31:50.120 --> 31:52.500
And who can be sent
to the doghouse

31:52.500 --> 31:54.460
when master wants to invite
his fancy friends over.

31:54.460 --> 31:56.040
Not at all --

31:56.040 --> 31:59.290
My turn to talk,
Cyrus.

31:59.290 --> 32:02.170
This is about
making up for that?

32:02.170 --> 32:03.460
Yes.
No.

32:03.460 --> 32:07.460
This is about
putting me back on the leash.

32:07.460 --> 32:11.620
I'm done
being your bitch, Cyrus.

32:11.620 --> 32:14.540
Time to switch positions.

32:14.540 --> 32:17.330
I'm on top now.

32:20.670 --> 32:22.830
Oh.

32:24.580 --> 32:28.290
You really thought
you could outsmart me, old man?

32:28.290 --> 32:29.500
A trained agent?

32:31.170 --> 32:34.120
Further proof
of your arrogance...

32:34.120 --> 32:36.620
your total disregard
for anyone

32:36.620 --> 32:39.040
who didn't go to your schools
or get into your clubs --

32:39.040 --> 32:40.500
We can --
[ Stammers ]

32:40.500 --> 32:42.580
Tom, please,
p-put down the gun.

32:42.580 --> 32:43.580
Why?
Just --

32:43.580 --> 32:45.000
Why?

32:45.000 --> 32:47.460
So you can pick it up
and shoot me?

32:47.460 --> 32:50.080
♪♪

32:50.080 --> 32:52.080
You deserve to die.

32:52.080 --> 32:55.710
More than anyone else
I have ever killed.

32:55.710 --> 32:58.830
You killed Frankie for me,
didn't -- didn't you?

32:58.830 --> 33:00.380
You did,
didn't you?

33:00.380 --> 33:02.000
I told...

33:02.000 --> 33:05.380
you not to,
but --

33:05.380 --> 33:09.210
I begged you not to,
but I -- I should have known

33:09.210 --> 33:13.380
that you would go
to that extreme...

33:13.380 --> 33:18.170
that you would kill him
to get me into the Oval.

33:20.790 --> 33:23.290
And I loved him.

33:24.790 --> 33:26.790
I loved Frankie.

33:26.790 --> 33:30.000
I loved that man.

33:30.000 --> 33:33.580
I never loved --
loved you.

33:33.580 --> 33:35.460
Ever.

33:35.460 --> 33:38.250
I used you.

33:42.500 --> 33:44.710
You loved me...

33:44.710 --> 33:46.670
and I used you.

33:46.670 --> 33:51.120
♪♪

33:55.670 --> 33:57.830
Open up.

33:58.960 --> 34:00.290
Aah!

34:02.580 --> 34:08.580
This is a much less efficient
way of killing you.

34:08.580 --> 34:10.960
Increased
margin of error.

34:10.960 --> 34:13.960
Increased likelihood
of you living --

34:13.960 --> 34:17.210
severely impaired,
of course.

34:17.210 --> 34:21.540
[ Breathing heavily ]

34:24.290 --> 34:26.790
[ Whimpers ]

34:26.790 --> 34:29.880
There are fates
worse than death.

34:29.880 --> 34:31.210
Much worse.

34:31.210 --> 34:33.120
And you should know.

34:33.120 --> 34:36.920
You handed one
to me.

34:36.920 --> 34:38.790
And now...

34:38.790 --> 34:40.210
I get
to hand it back.

34:44.880 --> 34:48.290
♪♪

34:55.210 --> 34:56.580
Cy.

34:56.580 --> 34:59.500
Cyrus.

34:59.500 --> 35:00.960
At least
have some breakfast.

35:02.880 --> 35:05.710
I don't want Ella
to see me like this.

35:05.710 --> 35:09.080
♪♪

35:17.750 --> 35:19.920
I'm not leaving you.

35:19.920 --> 35:22.080
I had plans...

35:22.080 --> 35:26.250
for when
I became President.

35:26.250 --> 35:29.380
How ridiculous
does that sound?

35:29.380 --> 35:31.420
When I became President.

35:31.420 --> 35:34.170
Me. I.

35:35.830 --> 35:40.880
[ Chuckles ]

35:42.540 --> 35:45.460
Cyrus...

35:46.710 --> 35:50.040
My first 100 days...

35:50.040 --> 35:53.500
would've rivaled...

35:53.500 --> 35:56.000
friggin' F.D.R.

35:59.420 --> 36:00.460
[ Chuckles ]

36:00.460 --> 36:02.420
I was gonna
tackle everything,

36:02.420 --> 36:08.420
from...healthcare
to energy reform...

36:08.420 --> 36:10.080
to education...

36:10.080 --> 36:13.830
to saving
this precarious economy

36:13.830 --> 36:17.380
that Fitzgerald Grant
never knew what to do with.

36:17.380 --> 36:19.540
I w--

36:21.210 --> 36:24.380
I would've been
downright transformational.

36:24.380 --> 36:27.580
[ Chuckles ]

36:27.580 --> 36:31.250
I had...plans.

36:31.250 --> 36:34.830
Families
would have my picture...

36:34.830 --> 36:37.750
hanging
in their dining rooms.

36:37.750 --> 36:41.330
Little kids
would tell their teachers

36:41.330 --> 36:45.170
they want to be me
when they grow up -- me --

36:45.170 --> 36:48.420
and not just
the gay ones.

36:48.420 --> 36:54.960
I mean, every last little boy
and girl in this country...

36:54.960 --> 36:58.540
would be looking up
to me.

36:58.540 --> 37:01.460
[ Chuckles ]

37:01.460 --> 37:03.330
Me. I.

37:03.330 --> 37:05.000
[ Chuckles ]

37:05.000 --> 37:10.080
Fat mouth-breathing "last picked
in gym class" Cyrus Beene.

37:10.080 --> 37:11.290
No...

37:11.290 --> 37:13.290
[ Chuckles ]

37:13.290 --> 37:17.580
De--
Delusions of grandeur.

37:17.580 --> 37:19.540
Like I said...

37:23.500 --> 37:24.880
...ridiculous.

37:26.330 --> 37:28.500
We can still
beat this.

37:29.830 --> 37:32.290
♪ God's a-gonna trouble
the water ♪

37:32.290 --> 37:33.710
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

37:33.710 --> 37:37.170
Mr. President?
Elizabeth North.

37:37.170 --> 37:39.120
Liz.
Elizabeth:
Mr. President.

37:39.120 --> 37:41.920
I understand you and Cyrus
worked out a deal the other day

37:41.920 --> 37:43.920
for him to step down
as President-Elect

37:43.920 --> 37:45.210
in exchange
for clemency.

37:45.210 --> 37:48.710
If the offer's still good,
he'd like to accept.

37:48.710 --> 37:50.080
♪ The water ♪

37:50.080 --> 37:52.080
Is the offer
still good?

37:52.080 --> 37:53.920
♪ Wade in the water, children ♪

37:53.920 --> 37:55.210
Unbelievable.

37:55.210 --> 37:58.330
So, he's admitting
to shooting Frankie Vargas?

37:58.330 --> 38:01.080
Under direct orders
from Cyrus Beene.

38:01.080 --> 38:06.500
♪ God's a-gonna trouble
the water ♪

38:06.500 --> 38:09.620
♪ Wade in the water ♪

38:09.620 --> 38:10.880
I'm sorry.

38:10.880 --> 38:12.250
You're gonna have to
repeat that.

38:12.250 --> 38:13.750
Slowly.

38:13.750 --> 38:18.620
Tom Larsen confessed
to the murder of Frankie Vargas.

38:18.620 --> 38:20.880
He will testify that Cyrus
ordered him to do it.

38:20.880 --> 38:23.040
The FBI is on their way
to Cyrus' house as we speak.

38:23.040 --> 38:24.500
And...

38:24.500 --> 38:26.290
And with Cyrus in jail,
the Electoral College

38:26.290 --> 38:30.290
will have no choice
but to vote for you.

38:30.290 --> 38:35.040
Mellie, you are the next
President of the United States.

38:35.040 --> 38:36.040
♪ God's a-gonna trouble
the water ♪

38:36.040 --> 38:39.670
[ Both chuckle ]

38:39.670 --> 38:42.620
♪ In the water, children ♪

38:42.620 --> 38:49.080
♪ Wade in the water ♪

38:49.080 --> 38:51.830
♪ God's a-gonna trouble
the water ♪

38:51.830 --> 38:53.250
Come on, Els.

38:53.250 --> 38:54.670
Let Daddy go.

38:54.670 --> 39:00.460
♪ See that band
all dressed in red ♪

39:00.460 --> 39:05.750
♪ God's a-gonna trouble
the water ♪

39:05.750 --> 39:10.960
♪ Looks like the band
that Moses led ♪

39:10.960 --> 39:16.580
♪ God's a-gonna trouble
the water ♪
[ Knock on door ]

39:16.580 --> 39:19.500
♪ Wade in the water ♪

39:19.500 --> 39:21.880
David: You have the right
to remain silent.

39:21.880 --> 39:23.540
Anything you say
can and will be used against you

39:23.540 --> 39:24.580
in a court of law.

39:24.580 --> 39:25.620
You have the right
to an attorney.

39:25.620 --> 39:27.210
If you cannot afford
an attorney,

39:27.210 --> 39:28.420
one will be appointed
for you.

39:28.420 --> 39:31.620
Do you understand?

39:31.620 --> 39:33.000
I need
a verbal confirmation.

39:33.000 --> 39:34.420
Yes.

39:34.420 --> 39:40.210
♪ God's a-gonna trouble
the water ♪

39:40.210 --> 39:44.290
♪ God's a-gonna trouble
the water ♪

39:44.290 --> 39:46.920
David Rosen?
I-I'm -- I'm not convinced.

39:46.920 --> 39:48.920
What is there
to be convinced of, Frankie?

39:48.920 --> 39:50.710
He'll make
a hell of a running mate.

39:50.710 --> 39:52.540
Not only
a seasoned Democrat

39:52.540 --> 39:55.250
but an integral part
of a Republican administration.

39:55.250 --> 39:57.670
[ Sighs ]
He's the best
of both worlds!

39:57.670 --> 39:59.830
Look, I don't know the guy.
I don't trust the guy.

39:59.830 --> 40:01.540
You know me.

40:01.540 --> 40:04.670
You trust me,
don't you?

40:04.670 --> 40:07.040
[ Chuckles ]
Well?

40:07.040 --> 40:08.790
Of course I trust you.

40:08.790 --> 40:13.380
Then you know
I would not steer you wrong!

40:17.460 --> 40:18.830
Look,
we're out of options.

40:18.830 --> 40:20.580
There's no time
to vet anyone else!

40:20.580 --> 40:22.880
Maybe we don't have to.

40:22.880 --> 40:24.000
What?

40:24.000 --> 40:26.790
Maybe we don't have to vet
anyone else

40:26.790 --> 40:30.000
because maybe I already know
all there is to know

40:30.000 --> 40:31.960
about the man that I want
as my Vice President.

40:33.620 --> 40:35.290
It's you, Cyrus.

40:35.290 --> 40:36.880
I want you...

40:36.880 --> 40:39.540
to be
my Vice President.

40:40.540 --> 40:42.000
You're serious?

40:42.000 --> 40:43.580
Yes.

40:43.580 --> 40:46.500
No!
No, no, I can't.

40:46.500 --> 40:48.120
I'm not --
[ Sighs ]

40:48.120 --> 40:49.540
I'm not
a politician!

40:49.540 --> 40:50.960
Good!

40:50.960 --> 40:52.210
I'm not good!

40:52.210 --> 40:55.040
That's the important thing.
I'm not a good guy.

40:55.040 --> 40:56.920
That's why
you're perfect.

40:56.920 --> 40:58.540
We complement
each other!

40:58.540 --> 41:00.080
You see
all the bad sides.

41:00.080 --> 41:01.710
I only ever see
the good.

41:01.710 --> 41:04.210
Y-You're making that mistake
right now.

41:04.210 --> 41:06.920
[ Chuckles ]
And you're honest.

41:06.920 --> 41:08.920
See?

41:08.920 --> 41:12.290
I am not gonna
let you say no, Cy.

41:12.290 --> 41:14.750
I want you by my side.

41:14.750 --> 41:17.620
I need you.
America needs you.

41:17.620 --> 41:20.170
So, what do you say,
Cy?

41:21.790 --> 41:23.790
Will you join me
on the ticket?

41:23.790 --> 41:26.290
You want me?

41:26.290 --> 41:28.330
I want you.

41:31.210 --> 41:33.380
Just say yes, Cy.

41:34.670 --> 41:36.710
Yes.

41:39.290 --> 41:42.710
It'd be both my honor
and my pleasure, Mr. President.

41:48.710 --> 41:50.120
[ Chuckles ]
Let's make it official,
then.

41:50.120 --> 41:50.920
Come on.

41:55.880 --> 42:00.290
I'll be right there.

